article.headline: NC Central 54, Delaware St. 43
article.story: DOVER, Del. -- Jeremy Ingram scored 20 points to lead North Carolina Central to a 54-43 win over Delaware State in a Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference game on Saturday, the Eagles' eighth consecutive victory. The winning streak ties the eight-game run from the 1996-97 season. Stanton Kidd had 13 points and 11 rebounds for the Eagles (14-7, 7-0). Casey Walker and Amere May had 11 each for the Hornets (9-11, 4-2), who had won three in a row. The Eagles shot 53.8 percent from the field (21 of 39) and outrebounded the Hornets 32-21. The Hornets shot 19 of 50 from the field. North Carolina Central also outshot Delaware State from the foul line, hitting 9 of 14 to Delaware State's 3 of 12. The Eagles outscored the Hornets 30-22 in the paint and 12-2 on fast-break points.
